      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ABODE'S TRILOGY (1) goes very well this trip starting 28 times for 11 wins and 12 minors. Missed the frame latest (22.14) when fifth over 390m at this track in a Free For All. Has the ability and looks a key chance here. PROCEEDING (2) struggled to get involved last start after settling well back at this track, but prior to that won comfortably by 5 lengths at this track (21.81) beating Maywyn's Chief in a Grade 5 on May 1. Form from her last run is proving strong. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. WICKET (8) charged out of the inside draw with a fast early sectional but swamped late when a close up fourth (16.88) at Healesville over 300m. Goes very well from this draw with five wins and four minor placings from 10 starts. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. SEAWAY CRUISER (7) recorded a commanding victory last time. Must be respected.",
